column5: Way to go  with the new jigs there Bubba .

Great job Glen!  Cant be too cold there...there are no parkas in the pics...LOL.  We are going crazy right now packing for our trip to Michigan. We leave first thing in the morning....  Will log on there I'm sure....hehe.  Alex...love the signature as well!! LOL
Nice fish...and damn nice hat there bubba! Joe
Your camera man's been into the houch again Bud !
Nice to see you got out... WTG  Thanks for sharing..
uhhhh thats a pretty small catfish bubba you got to get bigger bait if you want to get posted. Still a good day to be fishin though.  Art
Hmmmmm, were up here slippin & slidin in the snow & ice and your out fishing in a sweater.  ........life seems so unfair sometimes   Always enjoy your softwater reports thru the winter months, Dawg
nice fish, looks like you have a really neat fishery down there.
65 degrees n ur wearing a big sweater like that? that's shorts weather
Nice catch glen !!!!...can you please send some of that 65 degree temps up here !!!!!!!...dam i hate winter,i would be wearing shorts and hitting the beach,in those temps !!!..LOL..LOL..LOL
Nice Fish G, and sweater  Joey
Nice of you to wear a sweater of such warmth. Im sure, your thoughts were to make us feel better that you were freezing down there,but,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Hey,nice fish DAWG.

Well look at that the man from the land of Cotton is wearing alot of cotton right up to his neck.  65 degrees I would be in a T-Shirt dog but not in shorts like Shawn.This is coming from Shawn who can't wear a surivival suit cause he sweats too much.shawn are you sure you're not part Husky or something   Thanks for another fine report Glen and how do you keep that sweater so clean.Like Wayne says the camera man needs some help  MTP
Hey Dawg! Thanks for the report. Lookin' pretty spiffy there Bubba. May I have the phone number for Miss Joyce?
Hey, personally I can't believe he's actually wearing a sweater, and a great big thick one too!  (Nice fish btw!)
One question do kittenfish taste like chicken?
